Class Game

  • java.lang.Object
    • topLevelObjects.Game
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class Game
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable
    This is a Game object representing a game of CuteAndFluffy. It is created automatically when transitioning from a Lobby to a game.
    Author:
    Cody Lakin

      • Game

        public Game(java.lang.String givenName,
            CellMap givenMap,
            java.util.ArrayList<Team> givenTeams,
            java.util.ArrayList<Account> givenPlayers,
            GameMode givenMode)
        This constructor creates a Game object representing a game of CuteAndFluffy
        Parameters:
        givenMap - The given CellMap contains the present map size, terrain, wild units, and structures.
        givenTeams - The given list of Teams determines who is whose ally/enemy
        givenPlayers - The given list of Accounts keeps track of all human players in the game
        givenMode - The given GameMode contains user specified settings used to set up and run the game.

        public void run()
        This function will serve as the main loop of the game object. Here, the game logic will be run independently of the players. Player input will be received elsewhere, but it will be waited for here.
